# Ecosystem orientation {#ecosystem}

The **curveR** ecosystem contains three packages that share a common
data contract defined by curveRcore.
**curveRcore** provides the data structures, preprocessing pipeline
(`preprocess_standards()`), and settings constructors
(`new_antigen_constraints()`, `new_study_params()`, `new_fit_options()`)
used identically by both fitting engines.
**curveRbayes** (this package) fits Bayesian hierarchical dose–response
models via Stan and produces posterior concentration estimates with
full uncertainty propagation.
**curveRfreq** provides frequentist (nls/nlme) alternatives for
settings where speed or regulatory precedent is the primary concern;
a head-to-head comparison of both engines is in the
[ecosystem comparison vignette](../curveRcore/articles/ecosystem-comparison.html).

