# CDAN precision grids {#cdan-grids}

## What is a CDAN precision grid? {#cdan-concept}

**CDAN** (Concentration-Dependent Assay Noise)  [@omalley_theory_2003] [@omalley_bayesian_2008] precision profiling
characterises *how accurately* a calibration curve can back-calculate
an unknown concentration as a function of where that concentration
falls on the curve.
Near the inflection point the curve is steep — small response
uncertainty maps to small concentration uncertainty.
Near the asymptotes the curve is flat — the same response uncertainty
maps to large concentration uncertainty.

The CDAN grid makes this relationship explicit: a dense grid of
concentration values, each with its posterior predictive back-calculation
distribution and associated %CV, incorporating both curve-parameter
uncertainty *and* the additional measurement noise that a real
instrument observation would contribute.

## Accessing per-model grids {#grid-access}

For every converged, eligible model, `ensemble[[model]]$grid`
holds the pre-computed CDAN grid.
**This slot is always populated for all converged models when more
than one model is fitted**, enabling direct cross-model comparison
without re-running anything.

```{r grid-structure}
dplyr::glimpse(ensemble[["logistic4"]]$grid)
```

```{r grid-col-table, echo=FALSE}
tibble::tribble(
  ~Column,         ~Description,
  "curve_id",      "Integer FK — identifies which calibration curve this row belongs to.",
  "concentration", "log10(AU/mL) grid point — the x-axis value on the preprocessed scale.",
  "pred_mean",     "Posterior mean of the forward-predicted response at this concentration.",
  "pred_sd",       "Posterior SD of the forward-predicted response (parameter uncertainty only).",
  "pred_noise_sd", "Total predictive SD after Student-t noise injection (parameter uncertainty + measurement noise).",
  "cv_pct",        "% CV of back-calculated concentration at this grid point.",
  "model",         "Model identifier."
) |>
  knitr::kable(caption = "Columns in ensemble[[model]]$grid.")
```

```{r grid-plot,
    fig.cap="Per-model CDAN precision profiles: back-calculation %CV versus log10(concentration) for all curve_ids. The dashed line marks 20% CV — a typical regulatory acceptability threshold. The ribbon spans the range across curve_ids; the line is the mean."}
all_grids <- purrr::map_dfr(
  names(ensemble),
  function(m) {
    g <- ensemble[[m]]$grid
    if (is.null(g)) return(NULL)
    dplyr::mutate(g, model = m)
  }
)

all_grids |>
  dplyr::group_by(model, concentration) |>
  dplyr::summarise(
    cv_mean = mean(cv_pct,  na.rm = TRUE),
    cv_lo   = min(cv_pct,   na.rm = TRUE),
    cv_hi   = max(cv_pct,   na.rm = TRUE),
    .groups = "drop"
  ) |>
  ggplot(aes(x = concentration, colour = model, fill = model)) +
  geom_ribbon(aes(ymin = cv_lo, ymax = cv_hi),
              alpha = 0.15, colour = NA) +
  geom_line(aes(y = cv_mean), linewidth = 0.8) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 20, linetype = "dashed",
